The paper deals with game theory and network optimization, which are central topics in computer science. Specifically, it focuses on congestion games with uncertain delays, which falls under the category of game theory (cs.GT). The paper also discusses the impact of risk aversion on network routing, which is related to the field of network economics (cs.NE). Additionally, the paper uses combinatorial techniques to prove its results, which is a common approach in information theory (cs.IT) and theoretical computer science (cs.SI). Finally, the paper discusses the trade-off between short-term and long-term objectives, which is a topic that falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG).
